# Form Patterns

Forms in this project use React Hook Form with Zod validation and call server actions directly from JavaScript handlers.

## Form Component Structure

Use the `useForm` hook and `Form` component:

```typescript
'use client';

import { toast } from 'sonner';
import Form from '@/components/form/Form';
import InputText from '@/components/form/fields/InputText';
import useForm from '@/components/form/hooks/useForm';
import SubmitButton from '@/components/form/SubmitButton';
import { myAction } from '@/features/myfeature/actions/myAction';
import mySchema from '@/features/myfeature/schemas/mySchema';

function MyForm() {
  const form = useForm(mySchema, {
    submit: async (data) => {
      const { error } = await myAction(data);

      if (error) {
        toast.error(error.message);
      } else {
        toast.success('Success message');
        // Handle success (e.g., reset form, close modal, etc.)
      }
    },
  });

  const { isSubmitting } = form.formHook.formState;

  return (
    <Form form={form}>
      <InputText name="title" placeholder="Title" />
      <SubmitButton isSubmitting={isSubmitting}>Submit</SubmitButton>
    </Form>
  );
}
```

## Form Fields

Use form field components from `@/components/form/fields/`. These components integrate with React Hook Form using `Controller` and `useFormContext`.

### InputText Component

The `InputText` component is the base pattern for form fields:

```typescript
import { InputText } from '@/components/form/fields/InputText';

// With label
<InputText name="title" label="Title" placeholder="Enter title" required />

// Without label (label handled elsewhere)
<InputText name="email" placeholder="Email" type="email" />
```

### Creating Other Form Controls

Other form controls (DatePicker, Textarea, Select, Checkbox, Radio buttons, etc.) should follow the same pattern as `InputText`:

1. Use `Controller` from `react-hook-form` to integrate with the form
2. Use `useFormContext()` to access the form context
3. Wrap in `Field` component from `@/components/ui/field`
4. Use `FieldLabel` for labels (if needed)
5. Use `FieldError` to display validation errors
6. Accept `name` prop for the field name
7. Accept other props as needed (label, placeholder, etc.)

Example structure:

```typescript
import { Controller, useFormContext } from 'react-hook-form';
import { Field, FieldError, FieldLabel } from '@/components/ui/field';
import { YourUIComponent } from '@/components/ui/your-component';

type Props = {
  name: string;
  label?: string;
  // ... other props
};

export default function YourFormField(props: Props) {
  const { name, label, ...componentProps } = props;
  const { control } = useFormContext();

  return (
    <Controller
      name={name}
      control={control}
      render={({ field, fieldState }) => (
        <Field>
          {label && <FieldLabel>{label}</FieldLabel>}
          <YourUIComponent {...field} {...componentProps} value={field.value || ''} />
          <FieldError>{fieldState.error?.message}</FieldError>
        </Field>
      )}
    />
  );
}
```

Place new form field components in `src/components/form/fields/` directory.

## Form Validation

Validation happens in two places:

1. **Client-side**: Zod schema validation via React Hook Form resolver (automatic)
2. **Server-side**: Zod schema validation in server action (always validate on server)

### Schema Definition

```typescript
// features/myfeature/schemas/mySchema.ts
import { z } from 'zod/v4';

export const mySchema = z.object({
  title: z.string().min(1, 'Title is required').max(191),
  content: z.string().min(1, 'Content is required').max(1024),
  amount: z.coerce.number().positive('Amount must be positive'),
});

export type MyData = z.infer<typeof mySchema>;
```

### Using Schema in Form

The `useForm` hook automatically uses the schema for validation:

```typescript
const form = useForm(mySchema, {
  defaultValues: { title: '', content: '' },
  submit: async (data) => {
    // data is typed and validated
    await myAction(data);
  },
});
```

## Pending State

### In Forms

Use `isSubmitting` from React Hook Form's form state:

```typescript
const { isSubmitting } = form.formHook.formState;

<SubmitButton isSubmitting={isSubmitting}>Submit</SubmitButton>
```

### For Non-Form Actions

Prefer `useTransition()` over `useState()` for pending state:

```typescript
import { useTransition } from 'react';

function MyComponent() {
  const [isPending, startTransition] = useTransition();

  const handleAction = () => {
    startTransition(async () => {
      const result = await myAction();
      if (result.error) {
        toast.error(result.error.message);
      } else {
        toast.success('Success!');
      }
    });
  };

  return (
    <SubmitButton type="button" onClick={handleAction} isSubmitting={isPending}>
      Action
    </SubmitButton>
  );
}
```

## SubmitButton Component

The `SubmitButton` component:
- Accepts `isSubmitting` prop for pending state
- Can receive `type="button"` when used outside a form (for non-form actions)
- Automatically shows loading spinner when pending
- Can accept an `icon` prop

```typescript
// In a form
<SubmitButton isSubmitting={isSubmitting}>Submit</SubmitButton>

// Outside a form (button action)
import { ArrowLeftRightIcon } from 'lucide-react';

<SubmitButton
  type="button"
  onClick={handleAction}
  isSubmitting={isPending}
  icon={ArrowLeftRightIcon}
>
  Switch
</SubmitButton>
```

## Toast Patterns

### Same Page (No Redirect)

When the server action doesn't redirect, handle toasts in the form submit handler:

```typescript
const form = useForm(mySchema, {
  submit: async (data) => {
    const { error } = await myAction(data);

    if (error) {
      toast.error(error.message);
    } else {
      toast.success('Success message');
      // Handle success (reset form, close modal, etc.)
    }
  },
});
```

### With Redirect

When the server action redirects, **do not show success toast in the handler**. The server action should use `setCookie('toast', '...')` instead:

```typescript
// In form component - NO success toast
const form = useForm(mySchema, {
  submit: async (data) => {
    const { error } = await myAction(data);
    if (error) {
      toast.error(error.message);
    }
    // On success, action redirects - no need to handle here
  },
});

// In server action
'use server';

const myAction = async (data: MyData) => {
  // ... validation and database operations ...

  await setCookie('toast', 'Success message');
  redirect('/path');

  return actionSuccess();
};
```

The toast will be displayed on the redirected page via the toast cookie mechanism.

## Form Patterns

### Create Form

```typescript
function CreateForm() {
  const form = useForm(createSchema, {
    submit: async (data) => {
      const { error } = await createAction(data);
      if (error) {
        toast.error(error.message);
      } else {
        toast.success('Created successfully');
        form.formHook.reset();
      }
    },
  });

  const { isSubmitting } = form.formHook.formState;

  return (
    <Form form={form}>
      <InputText name="name" placeholder="Name" />
      <SubmitButton isSubmitting={isSubmitting}>Create</SubmitButton>
    </Form>
  );
}
```

### Edit Form

```typescript
function EditForm({ id, initialData }) {
  const form = useForm(updateSchema, {
    defaultValues: initialData,
    submit: async (data) => {
      const { error } = await updateAction(id, data);
      if (error) {
        toast.error(error.message);
      } else {
        toast.success('Updated successfully');
      }
    },
  });

  const { isSubmitting } = form.formHook.formState;

  return (
    <Form form={form}>
      <InputText name="title" placeholder="Title" />
      <SubmitButton isSubmitting={isSubmitting}>Update</SubmitButton>
    </Form>
  );
}
```

## Best Practices

1. **Always validate on server** - Client validation can be bypassed
2. **Use Zod schemas** - Single source of truth for validation
3. **Handle pending state** - Use `isSubmitting` from form state for forms, `useTransition()` for non-form actions
4. **Toast handling** - Show error toasts in handler, success toasts only if no redirect (use `setCookie` for redirects)
5. **Form reset** - Reset form after successful submission if staying on same page
6. **Type safety** - Export and use TypeScript types from Zod schemas
